cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.BIO. 

The paper deals with the reconstruction of evolutionary histories of genes based on homology relations, which involves graph theory and combinatorics. Therefore, cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the recognition and computation of a cotree, which falls under cs.LG (Learning) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper's application to biology suggests cs.BIO (Bioinformatics) as another possible sub-category.
